  "laws": [
    "L-P1 TERRITORY: Each worker_id owns its territory; others may read, not write the same scope cell.",
    "L-P2 MUTEX: At most one mutating worker active per mutex_group (integrator claim or GHA concurrency).",
    "L-P3 PIPELINE: Self-heal stages 1→5 are sequential handoffs; never duplicate an upstream stage.",
    "L-P4 DELEGATE: Cursor daily/weekly audits delegate machine proof to listed delegates_machine_to.",
    "L-P5 CLAIM: T1/T2/T3 agents must integrator-claim before editing shared scope_files.",
    "L-P6 KERNEL: Worker kernel routes one-shot tasks; it does not schedule loops or replace automations.",
    "L-P7 COPILOT: Copilot agent stays inside CODEOWNERS-fenced kaizen paths; never verifiers or laws."
  ]
